# Oliver Kullmann, 15.4.2005 (Swansea)

-------------------------------------------

Prerequisites (need to be installed):

GNU make, version 3.80 or higher
(check: run "make -v")

gcc and g++

the Qt library

-------------------------------------------

In case that system versions of the following programs/libraries
shall be used (instead of the local versions), the following
versions are supported:

g++, version 4.0.1 or higher
(tested: 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 4.0.3, 4.1.0, 4.1.1, 4.1.2)
(check: run "g++ -v")
Recommended: 4.1.2
Versions lower than 4.0.1 cannot compile the library
Problems:
 - 4.0.1 - 4.0.2, 4.1.0 fail for some foreign locales.
 - 4.0.1 - 4.0.2 do not detect all syntax errors (wrong handling
  of namespaces)

Boost, version 1_34_0 or higher
(tested: 1_34_0)
Recommended: 1_34_0
BOOST = path to the source library
(for example BOOST = /usr/local/include/boost-1_33/)

Doxygen, version 1.5.1 or higher
(tested: 1.5.1, 1.52)
(check: run doxygen --version)
Recommended: 1.5.2

Valgrind, version 3.1.0 or higher
(check: run valgrind --version)
Recommended: 3.2.3

Git, version 1.5.2 or higher
(check: run git --version)
Recommended: 1.5.2

----------------------------------------------

System requirements:

>= 512 MB main memory

Disc space:

For the full OKplatform, with some versions of gcc and Boost installed:
10 GB should be fully sufficient.

